<!-- Section 3: Benefits, Why Cupping Therapy Is The Natural Alternative -->
<section class="section section--tint s3-benefits">
  <div class="container">

    <h2 class="s3-benefits__heading">
      Why Cupping Therapy Is The Natural Alternative To Cosmetic Procedures
    </h2>

    <div class="s3-benefits__grid">

      <div class="s3-benefits__card">
        <h3 class="s3-benefits__card-title">Immediate Lifting and Firming Effects</h3>
        <p class="s3-benefits__card-body">
          The negative pressure created by cupping immediately stimulates blood flow and tissue oxygenation, creating a visible lifting and tightening effect. Many clients notice firmer, more contoured skin right after their first session, with improvements that continue to build over subsequent treatments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="s3-benefits__card">
        <h3 class="s3-benefits__card-title">Increased Blood Flow and Collagen Production</h3>
        <p class="s3-benefits__card-body">
          Cupping increases facial circulation by up to 400%, dramatically boosting oxygen and nutrient delivery to your skin cells. This surge in blood flow triggers your body's natural collagen synthesis, helping to rebuild the structural proteins that keep your skin plump, elastic, and youthful-looking.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="s3-benefits__card">
        <h3 class="s3-benefits__card-title">Natural Detoxification and Lymphatic Drainage</h3>
        <p class="s3-benefits__card-body">
          The gentle suction of cupping activates your lymphatic system, helping to flush out toxins, reduce fluid retention, and eliminate the puffiness that makes skin look tired and aged. This natural detoxification process leaves your complexion clearer, brighter, and more defined.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="s3-benefits__card">
        <h3 class="s3-benefits__card-title">Long-Lasting Anti-Aging Benefits</h3>
        <p class="s3-benefits__card-body">
          Unlike surface-level treatments, cupping works at the cellular level to create lasting change. A series of 4-6 treatments spaced 2 weeks apart can produce cumulative anti-aging benefits that rival more invasive procedures, with results that continue to improve as your skin's natural renewal processes are activated.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

